article.description:
Shareef Abdur-Rahim made all the big shots  down the stretch to help the Atlanta Hawks snap a seven-game
losing streak.
article.headline: Atlanta breaks seven-game losing streak
article.linkText: Hawks snap losing streak at Celtics' expense
article.story:
ATLANTA (Ticker) -- Shareef Abdur-Rahim made all the big shots 
down the stretch to help the Atlanta Hawks snap a seven-game
losing streak.

Abdur-Rahim scored 12 of his 25 points in the fourth quarter as
the Hawks held on for a 93-88 triumph over the Boston Celtics.

With 2:19 left, Abdur-Rahim hit a jumper to break an 83-83 tie.
Vin Baker made a layup at the other end to tie it, but
Abdur-Rahim responded by driving for a baby hook shot, then made
six free throws in the final minute.

Aside from a jumper by Jason Terry with 2:50 left, Abdur-Rahim
was the Hawks' only scorer over the last 4:22 as they avoided
their eighth loss this season when leading in the final five
minutes.

Dion Glover scored 18 points for Atlanta, which trailed until
Theo Ratliff dunked off an alley-oop feed from Dion Glover to
make it 58-56 with 3:49 to go in the third quarter.

The Celtics were unhappy when Boris Diaw clearly shuffled his
feet on an inbounds play with 21 seconds left and the Hawks
leading, 89-85.
